  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/dr-cou1-noncannulated-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/credibility-assessment-team-nagaraja",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required gradation level. One factor (Test conditions) achieved Gradation 1 against a required Gradation 2; this gap is accepted because the COU is explicitly bounded to static performance and the single ASTM F1717 load condition is directly representative. All QoI comparisons satisfy the pre-established acceptance bounds (relative difference <10%, E/uval <1.96). The FEA modeling framework is judged credible for the stated COU. Aleatory uncertainty sources are discussed narratively in the validation report; formal UQ artifacts are linked for selected results. Overall credibility is sufficient to support the Medium assurance level required for this Class II device application.",
